build:
STATIC, NO-CDN, NO-BUILD. One vendored ES module `rapp-go/catch.js` (pure logic + minting) + `rapp-go/catch.html` (runnable demo/AR-less harness so it stands alone). No network in the catch itself — the egg arrives already minted from the ENCOUNTER pipeline (open-meteo + momentToGenome), so catch is 100% on-device.

REUSED PLUMBING (copy the exact fns out of hologram/index.html into catch.js so the module is self-contained — no cross-page imports): `sha256hex`, the `canonical()` serializer, `genomeId`, `clamp`, `b64enc` (for deep-links), and the `keepToBasket` IndexedDB writer (db 'rapp-basket' v1, store 'eggs', keyPath 'id').

catch.js PUBLIC API (data models exact):
  const ORBS = { dew:{mult:.5,hold:1.2,label:'dew orb'}, standard:{mult:1,hold:1,label:'weather orb'}, bright:{mult:1.5,hold:.9,label:'bright orb'}, storm:{mult:2,hold:.8,label:'storm orb'}, dawn:{mult:6,hold:.4,label:'dawn orb'} };
  const AIDS = { none:{catch:1,flee:1}, calm:{catch:1.5,flee:.5,label:'calm berry'}, honey:{catch:2,flee:.7,label:'honey'}, golden:{catch:2.5,flee:.35,label:'golden berry'} };
  const TIERS = { COMMON:{base:.60,flee:.03}, UNCOMMON:{base:.42,flee:.06}, RARE:{base:.27,flee:.11}, LEGENDARY:{base:.15,flee:.18}, MYTHIC:{base:.08,flee:.25} };
  async function eggRarity(cart) → { tier, rarity01, s, hr, baseCatch, baseFlee }  // pure, deterministic
  function throwQuality(ratio, hit) → { hit, label:'Excellent|Great|Nice|normal', mult }
  function rollCatch({ tier, orb='standard', aid='none', throwMult=1 }) →
        { p, b, hit:true, consumedOrb:true, wobbles, caught, fled, fleeChance }
        // uses crypto rand; runs the 4-check loop then the flee check
  async function mintCaught(cart, meta) → keepToBasket(stampedCart) ; returns basket record
  Plus small event surface: pass callbacks {onWobble(i), onCaught(), onBreak(wobbles), onFlee()} into a `runCatch()` orchestrator that sequences timing (≈420ms/wobble) so the UI just renders.

crypto rand helper: `function rand(){const u=new Uint32Array(1);crypto.getRandomValues(u);return u[0]/4294967296;}`.

RING UI (catch.html, ~120 lines): a `<canvas>` overlaid on the encounter view; rAF loop draws R(t) pulse + the creature (drop in the existing software-3D player later, a placeholder disc for MVP); pointerdown starts a flick, pointerup = release → compute ratio + aim → throwQuality → if hit rollCatch → drive the wobble timeline via the callbacks. Device haptics via `navigator.vibrate(40)` per wobble (guarded). Audio via a 3-line WebAudio oscillator (no asset files). All inline, no external anything.

MINT-ON-CATCH (id stays honest): the egg is ALREADY a valid hologram-cartridge/1.0 with a content-hash id; catch must NOT touch `genome` (would change the id and break the "this IS that moment" contract). Attach provenance OUTSIDE the genome, exactly like `home`/`lineage` are kept outside today:
  stampedCart = { ...cart, caught:{ at:Date.now(), geohash:meta.geohash, place:meta.poiName||null, tier, orb, aid, throwLabel, wobbles } }
  then keepToBasket(stampedCart) → writes {id, egg:stampedCart, title, born:cart.born.from, addedAt} into the shared 'rapp-basket'/'eggs' store. Done — no other write path needed.

TUNING KNOBS all live in the three tables above (ORBS/AIDS/TIERS) + the two rarity constants (0.60/0.40) + bucket cutoffs — a designer tunes feel by editing those numbers, zero code changes.
